<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 28 at 6:22PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...LIGHT SNOW CONTINUES TO IMPACT THE EVENING COMMUTE...
Light snow showers will continue to impact the evening commute,
before tapering off late this evening. Given air temperatures in
the low 30s, slippery conditions remain possible, especially on
untreated roadways. Brief reductions in visibility also remain
possible in any heavier snow showers. Continue to use caution
while driving this evening and allow extra time to reach your
destination.</description>
